title = "Edge Computing and Content Delivery"

content = """
Quantum Flux Systems uses edge computing and content delivery networks (CDNs) to improve the performance and reliability of our global applications. These technologies allow us to process data and deliver content closer to our users, reducing latency and improving the overall user experience.

**CDN Integration:** We use CDNs (e.g., Cloudflare or AWS CloudFront) to cache and deliver static content such as images, videos, and scripts. This reduces the load on our origin servers and improves the performance of our applications for users around the world.

**Edge Computing for Low Latency:** We use edge computing platforms (e.g., AWS Lambda@Edge or Cloudflare Workers) to run code closer to our users. This allows us to perform tasks such as request filtering, header manipulation, and data processing at the edge, reducing latency and improving performance.

**Global Traffic Management:** We use global traffic management tools to route users to the nearest and most available edge location. This ensures that our applications remain performant and available even in the face of regional outages or high traffic loads.

**Security at the Edge:** We use edge security features such as WAF (Web Application Firewall), DDoS protection, and SSL/TLS termination to protect our applications from attacks at the edge. This reduces the load on our origin servers and improves the overall security of our applications.

**Operational Considerations for Edge Computing:** Edge computing introduces new operational challenges such as monitoring, debugging, and managing deployments across multiple locations. We use specialized tools and practices to address these challenges and ensure the reliability of our edge applications.
"""  # noqa: E501

version = "0.0.1"
